{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it mandatory for every workplace to have a specialist Domestic Abuse Lead",
        "additional_details": "There are concerns that domestic abuse has become a pandemic with no sign of containment. A Domestic Abuse Lead would raise awareness and bridge the gap before overstretched services step in, spotting early warning signs, assessing risk and providing next steps support. [With 1,800 suicides and two women killed weekly,] early workplace intervention could save lives and ease pressure on services.",
        "background": "Make it mandatory for every workplace to have a trauma-informed Domestic Abuse Lead responsible for raising awareness, recognising and evaluating risk, offering confidential support, and guiding safe next steps for anyone affected by abuse.",
